=head1 DESCRIPTION

Defines a track that determines which Amazon Redshift version to apply
after a new version is released. If the value for C<ServerlessTrack> is
C<current>, the workgroup is updated to the most recently certified
release. If the value is C<trailing>, the workgroup is updated to the
previously certified release.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 TrackName => Str

The name of the track. Valid values are C<current> and C<trailing>.


=head2 UpdateTargets => ArrayRef[L<Paws::RedshiftServerless::UpdateTarget>]

An array of C<UpdateTarget> objects to update with the track.


=head2 WorkgroupVersion => Str

The workgroup version number for the workgroup release.



